article.headline: Texas State 77, Alcorn State 71
article.story: SAN MARCOS, Texas (AP) -- Brandon Bush scored 18 points to help lead Texas State to a 77-71 victory Wednesday over Alcorn State, which remains winless on the season. Texas State (2-4) fell behind by four points early but managed to pull ahead and take a 36-25 lead at the break. Early in the second half, the Bobcats built 13-point lead, their largest of the game. Matt Fullenwider added 12 points for Texas State, while Antwoine Blanchard had 11 and Brent Holder had 10. Bush and Brandon Thomas led the Bobcats in rebounds with seven each. Delvin Thompson scored a game-high 26 points, including 10-of-13 free throws, and had five steals for Alcorn State (0-7). Juan Wyatt added 12 points and a game-high nine rebounds. Cornell Landry scored 11 and Clifton Douglas came off the bench to add 11.
